# Student Portal System

Web Development & Database Module | Week 8 Project

## 📌 Overview

This project is a Student Portal designed to manage student records, course enrollments, and academic data. It serves as a practical application for both:

* Web Development (Frontend \+ Backend)  
* Database Systems (CRUD API, Relational Modeling)

Built with a full-stack approach, it includes:  
✔ Frontend: Interactive UI (HTML/CSS/JavaScript)  
✔ Backend: RESTful API (Node.js/Express)  
✔ Database: Mysql (mysql workbench)
---

## 🛠 Tech Stack

### Frontend

* HTML5/CSS3 (Structure & Styling)  
* JavaScript (Dynamic UI Logic)  
* Bootstrap (Optional for responsive design)

### Backend

* Node.js (Runtime)  
* Express.js (API Framework)  
* RESTful Routing (CRUD Endpoints)

### Database

* SQLite (Default lightweight DB)  
* PostgreSQL (Optional for relational DB)  
* MongoDB (Optional for NoSQL)

### Tools

* Git (Version Control)  
* Thunder Client (API Testing)  
* VS Code (Development)

---

## 🚀 Development Process

### 1\. Setup & Installation

bash  
Copy  
Download  
\# Clone the repo  
git clone https://github.com/your-repo/student-portal.git

\# Install dependencies  
npm install express body-parser sqlite3  \# For SQLite backend

### 2\. Database Schema

Tables:

1. Students (id, name, email, enrollment\_date)  
2. Courses (id, code, title, credits, is\_active)  
3. Enrollments (id, student\_id, course\_id, grade, status)

### 3\. Backend API (Node.js/Express)

Example CRUD endpoint for Students:  
javascript  
Copy  
Download  
// GET all students  
app.get('/api/students', (req, res) \=\> {  
  db.all("SELECT \* FROM students", (err, rows) \=\> {  
    if (err) res.status(500).send(err);  
    else res.json(rows);  
  });  
});

### 4\. Frontend (UI Integration)

* Static Pages: index.html (Dashboard), students.html, courses.html  
* Dynamic JS: Fetch API calls to backend.

### 5\. Testing

* Manual Testing: Use Postman to verify API routes.  
* Database Checks: Confirm data integrity in SQLite Browser.
